    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all burned down to nothing but stubs of wax and grief. He is gone, and with him, the very light of my soul. I find myself staring into the darkness of this room and realizing... there is no more reason to wake to the sun. It would be so much more graceful, wouldn't it? To simply let the shadows take me, to fade away like the mist over the moors, rather than enduring this wretched, hollow existence.",
